Rating: 4
Really tasty. I follwed as written, except...accidently bought low-fat buttermilk (and didn't realize it..was trying to figure out why my batter was so sticky...added at least another 1/2c flour). Like several others, I did not add extra ginger to the top. I made them smaller - four circles of 8 each, turned the heat down to 400*, and baked for ~15 mins (Breville oven seems to bake fast). Given the amount of baking powder, they were rose a lot, and were still a very good size. I didn't take the fork rating down in spite of the stickiness, as I assume that was user error!

