Rating: 3
These were delicious, even more so if you love ginger! Melt in the mouth goodness, very forgiving of my less than light hand in kneading. A few notes: when I chopped the crystallized ginger in the Cuisinart, it tended to clump together so on adding it to the flour mixture I used my fingers to separate the clumpy bits. No buttermilk on hand so I used about three quarter cup sour cream and stirred in milk to make 1 cup. Used minced ginger from the jar rather than true fresh ginger - easier. This is definitely a winner on my list.

